West 163rd Street, north side, west from Fort Washington Ave., showing the southern extremity of the grounds of the New York Institution for the Deaf. This set consists of 3 views, No. 3 of which is in the opposite direction, being eastward from Riverside Drive.

June 15, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
